org.jivesoftware.smack.packet

Class Stanza

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jivesoftware.smack.packet.Stanza
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Element, Packet, TopLevelStreamElement
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    IQ, Message, Presence

    public abstract class Stanza
extends Object
implements TopLevelStreamElement, Packet
    Base class for XMPP Stanzas, which are called Stanza(/Packet) in older versions of Smack (i.e. < 4.1).

    Every stanza has a unique ID (which is automatically generated, but can be overridden). Stanza IDs are required for IQ stanzas and recommended for presence and message stanzas. Optionally, the "to" and "from" fields can be set.

    XMPP Stanzas are Message, IQ and Presence. Which therefore subclass this class. If you think you need to subclass this class, then you are doing something wrong.

    See Also:
    RFC 6120 ยง 8. XML Stanzas

      • DEFAULT_LANGUAGE

        protected static final String DEFAULT_LANGUAGE

      • language

        protected String language
        Optional value of the 'xml:lang' attribute of the outermost element of the stanza.

        Such an attribute is defined for all stanza types. For IQ, see for example XEP-50 3.7: "The requester SHOULD provide its locale information using the "xml:lang " attribute on either the (RECOMMENDED) or element."

      • getExtension

        public <PE extends ExtensionElement> PE getExtension(String elementName,
                                            String namespace)
        Returns the first extension that matches the specified element name and namespace, or null if it doesn't exist. If the provided elementName is null, only the namespace is matched. Extensions are are arbitrary XML sub-documents in standard XMPP packets. By default, a DefaultExtensionElement instance will be returned for each extension. However, ExtensionElementProvider instances can be registered with the ProviderManager class to handle custom parsing. In that case, the type of the Object will be determined by the provider.
        Specified by:
        getExtension in interface Packet
        Parameters:
        elementName - the XML element name of the extension. (May be null)
        namespace - the XML element namespace of the extension.
        Returns:
        the extension, or null if it doesn't exist.
